## Import

Boards can be imported using their ID, e.g.

```sh
 $ pulumi import honeycomb:index/board:Board my_board AobW9oAZX71
```

 You can find the ID in the URL bar when visiting the board from the UI.

honeycomb:index/burnAlert:BurnAlert.description:
## # Resource: honeycomb.BurnAlert

Creates a burn alert. For more information about burn alerts, check out [Define Burn Alerts](https://docs.honeycomb.io/working-with-your-data/slos/slo-process/#define-burn-alerts).

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}
### Basic Example

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as pulumi_honeycomb from "@materializeinc/pulumi-honeycomb";

const config = new pulumi.Config();
const dataset = config.require("dataset");
const sloId = config.require("sloId");
const exampleAlert = new honeycomb.BurnAlert("exampleAlert", {
    dataset: dataset,
    sloId: sloId,
    exhaustionMinutes: 480,
    recipients: [
        {
            type: "email",
            target: "hello@example.com",
        },
        {
            type: "slack",
            target: "#example-channel",
        },
    ],
});
```
